---
import WikiLayout from '../layouts/WikiLayout.astro';
import WikiCallout from '../components/WikiCallout.astro';
---

<WikiLayout title="Community PRD">
  <h1>Community PRD</h1>
  <p>This document governs the CURATIONS.DEV Vibe Coding Community. It outlines the product contract, our core loop, permission boundaries, and visual aesthetics.</p>
  
  <WikiCallout title="Authority">
    On merge, this document is the governing product contract for CURATIONS.DEV. It controls product purpose, the canonical social object, and public information architecture.
  </WikiCallout>

  <h2>1. The Product Contract</h2>
  <p>CURATIONS.DEV is a conversation-first Vibe Coding community where a builder shares a public GitHub Project and working plan, asks a human question, receives human and explicitly requested AI guidance, chooses what to use, and returns with a stronger plan or Project revision.</p>

  <pre><code>// The overarching goal
public Project + versioned working plan + human question
-> human and disclosed AI feedback
-> matched, source-linked artifacts</code></pre>

  <h2>2. Visual Oracle</h2>
  <p>We embrace a mix of editorial precision and brutalist architecture. We use <code>Instrument Serif</code> for massive, print-like headings, supported by <code>Inter</code> for readability, enclosed within unforgiving <code>2px</code> solid borders and offset shadows.</p>
</WikiLayout>
